author: lundblad
msg: Docstring tweak.
* subversion/include/svn_wc.h (svn_wc_entry_t): Point out that repos might be
NULL.

author: dlr
msg: A follow-up to r16141 for issue 2404 to avoid a segfault in working
copies created by 1.2.x and older series clients which have not had
'svn up' run on them to create the <entry repos="uri of server" ... />
attribute in .svn/entries files.  This change falls back to the
previous (slightly buggy) behavior until a 'svn up' is performed.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/copy.c
(svn_wc_copy2): Check both src_entry->repos and dst_entry->repos for
non NULL-ness before using their values to confirm that both copy
source and destination reside in the same repository.

author: dlr
msg: * subversion/tests/clients/cmdline/copy_tests.py
(wc_to_wc_copy_between_different_repos): Shorten doc string to less
than 50 characters to avoid a warning.

author: sussman
msg: * COMMITTERS:  change my email address.

author: cmpilato
msg: Begin teaching the "make path mutable" code how to use the pending
move IDs.  While this seems to resolve the primary key conflict
problem that shot down the naive atomic renames design, there's a
whoooole lotta thinkin' left to do here (meaning, I've recently
realized this is about to get rather tricky).
Branch: fs-atomic-renames
* subversion/libsvn_fs_base/dag.h,
* subversion/libsvn_fs_base/dag.c
(svn_fs_base__dag_entry_move_id): New.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_base/tree.c
(copy_id_inherit_fixed): New copy ID inheritence type.
(parent_path_t): Rename (and repurpose) the copy_src_path member to
copy_data.  Users updated.
(get_copy_inheritance): Rename (and repurpose) copy_src_path
variable to copy_data.  If fetching copy ID inheritence on
something whose parent stored a move ID for it, use that ID.
(make_path_mutable): Handle the new copy_id_inherit_fixed inheritence type.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_fs/fs-test.c
(move_test): Rework some comments.
(test_funcs): Expect move_test to PASS now (though, of course, it
won't on FSFS).
